div.p: How user actions become persisted state
1. User Action Types in TipTap editor, checks box, moves node
2. Svelte Handler OutlineItem calls outline.updateContent() or outline.moveNode()
3. API Bridge api.updateNode(id, changes) Tauri invoke
4. Rust Command commands::update_node() creates Operation::Update
5. Append Operation document.append_op() writes to pending.jsonl
pending.{host}.jsonl Append-only log
6. Apply Operation operations::apply() updates in-memory state
7. Return State DocumentState returned to frontend
8. Update UI outline.updateFromState() rebuilds tree cache
1. Load Request User opens document or app starts
2. Read state.json Base document state (last compacted)
state.json Merged state
3. Collect Pending Find all pending.*.jsonl from all machines
pending.*.jsonl Per-machine ops
4. Sort by Timestamp All ops sorted by updated_at (chronological)
5. Replay Operations Apply each op in order LWW for conflicts
6. Index for Search Background thread updates SQLite FTS5
SQLite FTS5 Search index
7. Render Tree Frontend builds tree, displays nodes
Machine A Edits offline
Machine B Edits offline
File Sync Dropbox/Syncthing syncs pending files
Merge on Load Both machines see all pending files
Conflict? Same node edited on both machines
LWW Resolution Latest updated_at wins (per-field granularity)
Compact User triggers compact: merge new state.json delete pending files
